<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="552" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1084,1972]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1767,1792]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Discussion.</emphasis>
The new species is allied 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu &amp; Zhang, 2000" authorityName="Liu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2000" box="[633,1220,1767,1792]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Xizicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parallelus" subGenus="Eoxizicus">
<emphasis box="[633,970,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Xizicus (Eoxizicus) parallelus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Liu" box="[986,1212,1767,1792]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552" refString="Liu, X. W. &amp; Zhang, W. N. (2000) Studies on Chinese katydids, I. Ten new species of the tribe Meconematini (Orthoptera: Tettigonioidea: Meconematidae) from China. Entomotaxonomia, 22 (3), 157 - 170." type="journal article" year="2000">
Liu &amp; Zhang, 
<number box="[1152,1212,1768,1792]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from the latter in: male cercus middle part of inner margin with a lamellar process, the edge sinuate; near basal part of ventral margin with a long and flat process, the apex broader; styli stout nd long on almost a fourth apical area of lateral margins of subgenital plate, nearly conical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="552" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1084,1972]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1911,1936]" pageId="4" pageNumber="552">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species is derived from the morphology of the inner process of the male cercus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
